{"title":"MXC or Moots Cross-Country: All-New Light Titanium Hardtail Race Bike from Steamboat","link":"https://bikerumor.com/mxc-or-moots-cross-country-all-new-light-titanium-hardtail-race-bike-from-steamboat/","date":1717187920000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_Steamboat-Springs-Colorado-workshop_Made-in-USA-1536x1024.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"2024 Moots MXC lightweight cross-country hardtail, US-made titanium in Steamboat Springs. CO\" /></p>\n<p>I feel like it’s been decades since I last saw a new ti Moots XC hardtail, but this MXC means the Colorado bike builder still has cross-country racing on the brain. Their PR team hints it could be prepping for Olympic racing, but Moots also describes the new bike as their “most progressive XC bike yet”. Any way you shake it, this new Moots MXC cross-country hardtail looks quick – whether you plan on racing hot laps on your local singletrack or heading to Paris to hunt for some shiny Gold to play off this matte titanium…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>2024 Moots MXC lightweight ti cross-country hardtail</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_classic-XC-race-bike_head-badge.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_classic-XC-race-bike_head-badge.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Moots MXC lightweight cross-country hardtail, head badge\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_classic-XC-race-bike_head-badge.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_classic-XC-race-bike_head-badge-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_classic-XC-race-bike_head-badge-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_classic-XC-race-bike_head-badge-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_classic-XC-race-bike_head-badge-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_classic-XC-race-bike_head-badge-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_classic-XC-race-bike_head-badge-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/Moots)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>“<em>The MXC is the solution to riders looking for a lightweight titanium hardtail designed for buff trails, demanding climbs, hours of hard pedaling, and those areas in the world where “downcountry” trends don’t apply.</em>“</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_race-bike.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_race-bike.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Moots MXC lightweight cross-country hardtail, fast race bike detail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_race-bike.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_race-bike-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_race-bike-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_race-bike-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_race-bike-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_race-bike-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Yeah, just looking at it, and it’s clear this a rabid race bike. Moots calls the MXC progressive, but that just means its up for modern XC racing. That means it’s 1x specific, it’s got room for high-volume 29 x 2.4″ race tires, a racy steep 69° head angle, but built for a 100mm fork. Think of it as an updated Mooto X &amp; MX RSL, mashed together with extra tire clearance, a bit longer fork, and slightly more modern geo.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_frame-crop.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_frame-crop.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Moots MXC lightweight cross-country hardtail, frame cropped\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_frame-crop.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_frame-crop-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_frame-crop-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_frame-crop-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_frame-crop-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_frame-crop-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_frame-crop-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>“<em>Think Leadville 100, Chequamegon, and Sea Otter Classic—fast, efficient, and fun.</em>“</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It certainly isn’t a trail hardtail, though. There’s still the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/moots-womble-widens-tire-clearance-tubing-for-aggressive-new-titanium-hardtail/\" target=\"_blank\">Womble</a> aggressive trail bike for that, with a 140mm fork, fatter tires, and slacker geometry. But, IFYKYK.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tech details</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_angled-rear.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1536\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_angled-rear-1536x1536.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Moots MXC lightweight cross-country hardtail, angled rear end\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_angled-rear-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_angled-rear-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_angled-rear-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_angled-rear-768x768.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_angled-rear.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_rear-end-detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_rear-end-detail.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Moots MXC lightweight cross-country hardtail, raer end detail up close\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_rear-end-detail.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_rear-end-detail-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_rear-end-detail-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_rear-end-detail-768x768.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_T47-threaded-BB.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_T47-threaded-BB.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Moots MXC lightweight cross-country hardtail, T47 bottom bracket\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_T47-threaded-BB.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_T47-threaded-BB-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_T47-threaded-BB-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_T47-threaded-BB-768x768.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>4 stock sizes (S-XL)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Lightweight titanium tubeset with a double-butted front triangle &amp; S-bend seatstays</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Straight 44mm matched headtube for a Chris King headset and 1.5″ tapered steerer</li>\n\n\n\n<li>T47 threaded bottom bracket</li>\n\n\n\n<li>max 38T chainring</li>\n\n\n\n<li>30.9mm seatpost, with internal dropper post routing</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Boost 12x148mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>160mm Post Mount disc brake</li>\n\n\n\n<li>UDH (Universal Derailleur Hanger)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fully external rear brake routing, optional mechanical shift routing</li>\n\n\n\n<li>up to 3 sets of water bottle cage mounts for full marathon mode</li>\n\n\n\n<li>max 29 x 2.4” tires</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_geometry.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_geometry.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Moots MXC lightweight cross-country hardtail, XC race geometry\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_geometry.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_geometry-297x124.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_geometry-120x50.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_geometry-768x320.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Moots MXC ti hardtail – Pricing, options &amp; availability</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_complete.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_complete.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Moots MXC lightweight ti cross-country hardtail, complete titanium race bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_complete.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_complete-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_complete-1536x922.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_complete-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_complete-768x461.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Complete Moots MXC bikes start at $9,999. But with that, you already get a full XTR groupset, SID Ultimate fork, and Astral Outback carbon wheels! Sure, you can also opt for SRAM &amp; AXS wireless if you are looking for something more techy, but heavier, more complex, and reliant on you keeping batteries charged. An XX SL AXS build with Zipp 1Zero wheels will run you at least $11,200.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_Frostbite-custom-finish.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_Frostbite-custom-finish.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Moots MXC lightweight cross-country hardtail, custom Frostbite anodized titanium finish\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_Frostbite-custom-finish.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_Frostbite-custom-finish-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_Frostbite-custom-finish-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_Frostbite-custom-finish-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_Frostbite-custom-finish-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Moots-MXC-lightweight-cross-country-hardtail_Frostbite-custom-finish-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A <a href=\"https://moots.com/bikes/mountain/mxc/\" target=\"_blank\">thousand dollars down</a> will get you a build slot, and kick your new Moots MXC into production. Then you have to think if you want to upgrade from the classic Moots bead blasted ti finish to something like this thousand dollar extra Frostbike look!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://moots.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Moots.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/mxc-or-moots-cross-country-all-new-light-titanium-hardtail-race-bike-from-steamboat/\">MXC or Moots Cross-Country: All-New Light Titanium Hardtail Race Bike from Steamboat</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"f7632c80a66a3ab37096ffe2ceedc9c28b9e1d4f9c2b54e5227ef6870a2a3972","category":"Cycling"}